                <h1>Exploring the Symbolism in "The Yellow Wallpaper"</h1>
                <p>In "The Yellow Wallpaper," the protagonist's point of view reveals her descent into madness as she grapples with repression and the constraints of 19th-century gender roles. The wallpaper symbolizes her entrapment, reflecting her struggle for identity and freedom. Through her observational lens, we explore themes of isolation, mental health, and the fight for autonomy.</p>
